HEADWORD: Estrangement
<hw>Es*trange"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>estrangement</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of estranging, or the state
of being estranged; alienation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>estrangement</qex> from God.</q> <rj><qau>J. C.
Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A long <qex>estrangement</qex> from better things.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Estranger</ent>⟦br⟧
